{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic"]]},"metadata":{"title":"MultipleColorSemanticToken","role":"symbol","externalID":"c:@M@OUDSTokensSemantic@objc(cs)MultipleColorSemanticToken","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MultipleColorSemanticToken","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MultipleColorSemanticToken"}],"symbolKind":"class","roleHeading":"Class","modules":[{"name":"Tokens for semantics"}]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/objc(cs)NSObject"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/objc(pl)NSObject","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s7CVarArgP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s28CustomDebugStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/SQ","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/SH","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s16SendableMetatypeP"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleColorSemanticToken"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MultipleColorSemanticToken","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["        \/\/ Assuming in Figma with have a color semantic token bgPrimary,","        \/\/ two semantic color tokens will be defined in Figma and generated by tokenator.","        \/\/ They can be declared in protocol ColorSemanticTokens,","        \/\/ and defined automaticaly in OUDSTheme+ColorSemanticTokens extension","        var bgPrimaryLight: ColorSemanticToken { ColorRawTokens.functionalWhite }","        var bgPrimaryDark: ColorSemanticToken { ColorRawTokens.functionalDarkGray880 }","","        \/\/ Then the develoment team declares an \"higher\" level color semantic token for bgPrimary","        \/\/ inside ColorMultipleSemanticTokens protocol,","        \/\/ and defined inside OUDSTheme+ColorMultipleSemanticToken extension","        var bgPrimary: MultipleColorSemanticToken { MultipleColorSemanticToken(light: bgPrimaryLight, dark: bgPrimaryDark) }","","        \/\/ If the same color is used whatever the color scheme is","        var bgPrimary: MultipleColorSemanticToken { MultipleColorSemanticToken(bgPrimaryLight) }","","        \/\/ The theme exposes both generated color semantic tokens and \"crafted\" higher level color semantic tokens.","        \/\/ It is recommended to use the higher level version as it is less error-prone."]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["     @Environment(\\.theme) var theme","     @Environment(\\.colorScheme) var colorScheme","","    \/\/ Given you want to apply the color token \"surfaceBrandPrimary\"","    var body: some View {","        \/\/ Apply the token of color for the view without managing yourself the color scheme","        SomeView()","            .background(theme.colors.surfaceBrandPrimary)","","        \/\/ Or also foregroundStyle(), foregroundColor(), accentColor(), ...","    }"]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ Or get the token depending to the color scheme and do whatever you want with","    theme.colors.surfaceBrandPrimary.color(for: colorScheme)"]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"0.8.0","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Since","style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Kind of semantic tokens which will wrap a combination of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/ColorSemanticToken"},{"type":"text","text":" depending to "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"color scheme","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" (i.e. ligh mode or dark mode)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Kind of composite token with multiple values, but not named “composite” because this word is already used in the design system."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Allows to gather the multiple-value tokens from "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figma","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" inside one object."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If a color token exists with its value depending to the color scheme, it must be packed in such ``MultipleColorSemanticToken`"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/multiplecolorsemantictoken"]}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleColorSemanticToken\/init(_:)","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleColorSemanticToken\/init(light:dark:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleColorSemanticToken\/dark","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleColorSemanticToken\/light"],"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleColorSemanticToken\/color(for:)","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleColorSemanticToken\/hasForbiddenColorValue()","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleColorSemanticToken\/isEqual(_:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Instance Methods",